   Modifications To The Compiler: GNU_Native_4.8_C++ And Its Child Nodes
   ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      1. Start VectorCAST on your local computer
      2. Open the VCS21 project
      3. Modify the following nodes under the GNU_Native_4.8_C++ Compiler node


         Node: GNU_Native_4.8_C++ Compiler
         ─────────────────────────────────
            1. Using your mouse, right click on the configuration options icon to the right of the node.
               Select the "Linker options" menu item from the pop-up menu. This action will open the "Configuration" tab.
            2. Verify that the following parameters are in the "Linker options:" text box (all parameters WILL be on one line,
               but are shown below on multiple lines for clarity):

                  -Wl,-Map,vcast.map $(VCAST_VCS21_SRC_BASE)/third_party/agent++/lib/i386/libagent++.so
                  $(VCAST_VCS21_SRC_BASE)/third_party/snmp++/lib/i386/libsnmp++.so -lpthread -lcrypto -llttng-ust


         Test Suite Nodes
         ────────────────
            1. For each Test Suite Node under the compiler node (see above diagram), repeat the following steps
            2. Using your mouse, hover over the configuration options icon to the right of the node.
            3. If there are "Linker options:", right click on the configuration options icon to the right of the node and select
               the "Clear Single Option -> Linker options:" menu item from the pop-up menu.
            4. Repeat step two and verify that there are no "Linker options:" listed.


         Unit Test Environment Nodes
         ───────────────────────────
            1. For each Unit Test Node under each Group node under the compiler node (see above diagram),
               repeat the following steps
            2. Using your mouse, hover over the configuration options icon to the right of the node.
            3. If there are "Linker options:", right click on the configuration options icon to the right of the node and select
               the "Clear Single Option -> Linker options:" menu item from the pop-up menu.
            4. Repeat step two and verify that there are no "Linker options:" listed.
